{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-doc-page-js","path":"/goals/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"auxeng-program-high-level-goals\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#auxeng-program-high-level-goals\" aria-label=\"auxeng program high level goals permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>AuxEng Program High-Level Goals</h2>\n<p>AuxEng is an internal consulting program structure which helps platform teams get significantly closer to the teams they enable. This often helps the platform team <a href=\"platforms/\">identify previously unknown opportunities</a> to improve other teams’ effectiveness. In other cases, it can be useful to debug a team’s reluctance to adopt a new tool, or a drift away from best practices.</p>\n<p>In addition to the primary goals, there are multiple secondary goals which are also valuable to organizations:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It’s an effective way of creating <a href=\"mobility/\">mobility of engineering talent</a> across the organization.</li>\n<li>It can provide an attractive <a href=\"careers/\">engineering role archetype</a> for the organization’s most experienced software engineers.</li>\n<li>In addition to those, there are several other <a href=\"diffusion/\">organizational benefits</a> we’ve observed in the dozens of engagements we’ve run.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"engagement-goals\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#engagement-goals\" aria-label=\"engagement goals permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Engagement Goals</h2>\n<p>Engagements can sometimes have different goals under different circumstances. Sometimes those goals will change how the engagement is run. For example, sometimes a shorter engagement of only a few weeks is sufficient to identify why a software team’s commit size is increasing while their engineering cycle times are growing longer.</p>\n<p>We’ve used AuxEng to embed with an early adopter of a new tool, creating a tight and clear feedback loop which expedites early iterations. The embedded engineer can see firsthand how the tool is succeeding (or not) in achieving its desired outcomes.</p>\n<p>Here are a few example goals we’ve come across for specific engagements:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Drive adoption of a tool or best practice</li>\n<li>Rally around a key business strategic goal with minimal disruption to other work streams</li>\n<li>Partner with an early adopter to understand how a new solution is being used</li>\n<li>Debug a behavioral or tooling issue that has been identified</li>\n<li>Spread knowledge and awareness of a new technology or skill set</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/goals/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Engagement Goals","image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/fcb4df312ea3e87a9d57ffaf89a97635/87cb2/goals.png","height":400,"width":600}}}}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"5a71defc-9aea-5079-91fa-fa9e953f51bd","fields":{"slug":"/example/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Example Engagement"},"parent":{"relativeDirectory":""}}},{"node":{"id"